<p>Concept source receipt</p>
<p>Source: d2l-linear-algebra</p>
<p>Given two vectors $\mathbf{x}, \mathbf{y} \in \mathbb{R}^d$, their dot product $\mathbf{x}^\top \mathbf{y}$ (also known as inner product, $\langle \mathbf{x}, \mathbf{y}  \rangle$) is a sum over the products of the elements at the same position: $\mathbf{x}^\top \mathbf{y} = \sum_{i=1}^{d} x_i y_i$.</p>

