<item ID="1784483370" Creator="Beau Boorman" proto="ALG Concept" >
<attribute name="ALGId" >softmax-ordering</attribute>
<attribute name="ALGKind" >concept</attribute>
<attribute name="ALGPrerequisites" >softmax</attribute>
<attribute name="ALGQuotedText" >Moreover, because the softmax operation preserves the ordering among its arguments, we do not need to compute the softmax to determine which class has been assigned the highest probability.</attribute>
<attribute name="ALGSourceId" >d2l-softmax-regression</attribute>
<attribute name="ALGTags" >argmax;classification;ordering;softmax</attribute>
<attribute name="ALGTitle" >Softmax Preserves Ordering</attribute>
<attribute name="Created" >2026-07-19T12:49:19-05:00</attribute>
<attribute name="DominantLanguage" >en</attribute>
<attribute name="Height" >2.5</attribute>
<attribute name="Modified" >2026-07-19T12:49:19-05:00</attribute>
<attribute name="NLNames" >Aston Zhang</attribute>
<attribute name="NLOrganizations" >Lipton</attribute>
<attribute name="NLPlaces" >Alexander</attribute>
<attribute name="Name" >Softmax Preserves Ordering</attribute>
<attribute name="ScreenHeight" >67</attribute>
<attribute name="ScreenWidth" >132</attribute>
<attribute name="Sentiment" >-0.5882353073</attribute>
<attribute name="Sentiments" >-0.4;-0.6;-0.8;-0.6;-0.8;-0.4;-0.6;-0.8;-0.6;-0.6;-0.4;-0.6;-0.8;-0.8;-0.4;-1;0.2</attribute>
<attribute name="Width" >5</attribute>
<attribute name="Xg" >0.2038837092</attribute>
<attribute name="Xpos" >14</attribute>
<attribute name="Yg" >0.2606382129</attribute>
<attribute name="Ypos" >8.5</attribute>
<text >Softmax preserves score ordering, so the largest input score identifies the class with the highest output probability.

Lesson: Softmax Keeps Scores in the Same Order

Step 1 (core)
Softmax keeps its input scores in the same order.
Source: d2l-softmax-regression
Quoted passage:
the softmax operation preserves the ordering among its arguments

Step 2 (core)
So you can identify the class with the highest probability without calculating softmax.
Source: d2l-softmax-regression
Quoted passage:
we do not need to compute the softmax to determine which class has been assigned the highest probability

Concept source receipt
Source: d2l-softmax-regression
Moreover, because the softmax operation preserves the ordering among its arguments, we do not need to compute the softmax to determine which class has been assigned the highest probability.

Adapted (translated to plain English; atomized into concept lessons) from Dive into Deep Learning — 4.1 Softmax Regression by Aston Zhang, Zachary C. Lipton, Mu Li, and Alexander J. Smola, CC-BY-SA-4.0 (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/).</text>
<html ><![CDATA[<p>Softmax preserves score ordering, so the largest input score identifies the class with the highest output probability.</p>

<p>Lesson: Softmax Keeps Scores in the Same Order</p>

<p>Step 1 (core)</p>
<p>Softmax keeps its input scores in the same order.</p>
<p>Source: d2l-softmax-regression</p>
<p>Quoted passage:</p>
<p>the softmax operation preserves the ordering among its arguments</p>

<p>Step 2 (core)</p>
<p>So you can identify the class with the highest probability without calculating softmax.</p>
<p>Source: d2l-softmax-regression</p>
<p>Quoted passage:</p>
<p>we do not need to compute the softmax to determine which class has been assigned the highest probability</p>

<p>Concept source receipt</p>
<p>Source: d2l-softmax-regression</p>
<p>Moreover, because the softmax operation preserves the ordering among its arguments, we do not need to compute the softmax to determine which class has been assigned the highest probability.</p>

<p>Adapted (translated to plain English; atomized into concept lessons) from Dive into Deep Learning — 4.1 Softmax Regression by Aston Zhang, Zachary C. Lipton, Mu Li, and Alexander J. Smola, CC-BY-SA-4.0 (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/).</p>]]></html>
</item>
